<paragraph blockId="51.[138,1185,1607,1663]" pageId="51" pageNumber="2969">
Known only from a single female, this species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mound &amp; Minaei" authorityYear="2007" box="[962,1102,1607,1631]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Podothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="2969" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis box="[962,1102,1607,1631]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="2969">P. anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is unusual in having most of the major setae acute.
</paragraph>
